g.text: This workflow is based on the FeatureFinderIdentification approach published in Weisser et al., 2017. It's
supposed to be superior to conventional feature finding by matching all (consensus) identifications to
features in all runs. It is a feature propagation algorithm just like DemixQ. Essential steps:
- RT normalize mzML runs before searching using e.g. MapAlignerPoseClustering/MapAlingerIdentification
- merge all identifications from all runs using IDmerger
- use FeatureFinderIdentification with IDs from a single 'consensus' idXML file
- FeatureLinkerUnlabelledKD links features from different maps/runs and was superior to FLU-QT
- ConsensusMapNormalizer normalizes total intensity between different maps/runs
ID MERGING - separate workflow necessary to fix bug: replace 'value =
[list of files]' with a single file name in field 'spectra_data' in merged idXML
